This paper proposes an interpretable model for credit risk assessment, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also focuses on providing globally consistent explanations for the model, which suggests a focus on interpretability and transparency. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper mentions a new online visualization tool, which suggests a focus on data visualization and analysis, making cs.CY (Computers and Society) a likely sub-category as well. Finally, the paper also mentions subscales and nonlinearities, which suggests a focus on mathematical modeling and analysis, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category.
